The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Mumbai: The controversial Umpires Decision Review System (UDRS) would not be used during Indias upcoming Test tour of South Africa.    
	There wont be any UDRS (during the series), said BCCIs chief administrative officer, Prof. Ratnakar Shetty.    
	The ICC had left it to the two boards  BCCI and Cricket South Africa (CSA) to deal with the issue, though normally its the prerogative of the home countrys board.         
	Islamabad: Pakistan has recalled former captain Younis Khan for next months Twenty20 Internationals against New Zealand. Chief selector Mohsin Khan said that the squad for the six ODIs against New Zealand will be announced later.    
	The Squads    
	Twenty20: Shahid Afridi (capt.), Mohammed Hafeez, Ahmed Shahzad, Younis Khan, Umar Akmal, Fawad Alam, Adnan Akmal, Saeed Ajmal, Abdur Rehman, Abdul Razzaq, Umar Gul, Shoaib Akhtar, Tanvir Ahmed, Sohail Tanvir, Wahab Riaz (subject to fitness).    
	Test: Misbah-ul-Haq (capt.), Mohammed Hafeez, Taufiq Umar, Younis Khan, Azhar Ali, Asad Shafiq, Umar Akmal, Adnan Akmal, Saeed Ajmal, Abdur Rehman, Umar Gul, Tanvir Ahmed, Sohail Tanvir, Wahab Riaz (subject to fitness).         
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has expressed reservations on the new Future Tours Programme over lesser number of matches allotted to the national side against top teams, including India, at the ICC chief executives meeting in Dubai on Tuesday.         
	Karachi: The participation of Pakistani players in the fourth edition of the Indian Premier League remains in doubt with a top BCCI official on Tuesday saying that it is yet to take a decision on the issue.    
	Although the players auction for IPL IV will be held in Mumbai on January 8 and 9, the BCCI is yet to reach a decision on whether to allow Pakistani players in the tournament.         
	New Delhi: Royal Challengers Bangalore owner Vijay Mallya slammed the BCCI, saying that the rules and regulations for the Indian Premier League were made without the consultation of the franchisees involved.         
	New Delhi: Teen sensation Vikas Krishan, who ended Indias 12-year-old wait for a boxing gold at the Asian Games, on Tuesday said he never expected to clinch the yellow metal considering he was fighting his first international event at the senior level.    
	I thought I would do well for myself but that I would get a gold was not what I had expected. I cant tell you how happy I am, Vikas said.         
	New Delhi: The Indian eves suffered their second consecutive defeat at the World Team Squash championship when they were drubbed 0-3 by second-seeded Australia in Palmerston North, New Zealand.    
